Echo Server
    An EchoServer is an application that allows a client 
and a server to connect so a client can send a message to
the server and the server can receive the message and send,
or echo, it back to the client.
In this case server send back received message to client.

Usage:
Before Start Server/client
Check line 6 in echoClient.py and line 10 in echoServer.py same
1: Start Server( python echoServer.py)
2: Start client(python echoClient.py)
    Server allows 5 connection(echoServer.py line 3)
3:Send a message entering console from client 
